  "video_path": "/Users/bherms/src/japan/data/raw/DTgOTxUjxdP/2026-01-14_20-19-32_UTC.mp4",
  "caption": "Where To Shop in Tokyo🇯🇵 #tokyoguide #shoppingguide #fashion #drewjoiner #traveljapan",
  "transcript": "If you're ever planning to visit Tokyo, here are the shops that you should 100% add to your list. First, if you're interested at all in Japanese denim, selvedge denim, or Japanese jeans, Hanoia is your one-stop shop for it all. Nestled underneath Ueno Station's train tracks, this shop carries legendary brands such as Momotaro Jeans and Big John, and so much more. And while in this area, you can also visit the Ameyoko Market and Amerikaya, which is another fantastic Japanese Americana shop. On my most recent visit to Japan, I fell in love with the Nakamegoro neighborhood. General Store is this sort of fashion speakeasy that looks incredibly unassuming until you walk in. Iki is a women's wear shop that carries classic pieces with a twist. And while you're walking on the Megoro River, being enchanted by the cherry blossoms or the foliage, make sure you stop into Vizvum and Nigel K. Bourne. If you enjoy interior design, you'll particularly love Vizvum. If you have the time, I highly recommend taking the one-hour-ish train ride south of Tokyo to Kamakura. And when you're there, visit the Leather Goods Shop with Yugahama. It's this very tiny shop run by this older gentleman, but the selection there is both timeless and high quality. Last, if you love vintage shopping or thrifting and you don't just want to be in Harajuku or Shibuya, then you must visit Shimokitazawa. North of the station, you want to add Raglamagla to your maps and just walk through and pop in different shops. South of the station, you want to add Mirage Vintage. I'd almost say visiting Shimokitazawa without having too many specific shops that you want to visit is the way to go because once you're there, there's going to be so much density of vintage that just explore and have a good time. Let me know if you want a part two focused on Kyoto and Osaka.",
  "transcript_segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 5.46,
      "text": "If you're ever planning to visit Tokyo, here are the shops that you should 100% add to your list."
